22-12-09T14:33:35Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "### What needs to be fixed?\nI'm told that `eprint!` should often be paired with `io::stdout().flush()` just like `print!`, but the docs don't mention that.\n\n### Page(s) Affected\nhttps://doc.rust-lang.org/std/macro.print.html recommends buffer flushing, but https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/macro.eprint.html doesn't.\n\n### Suggested Improvement\nWe should copy/paste the buffer flush note from `print!` docs to `eprint!` docs (and change `stdout` to `stderr`). (I would submit a PR to do this, but I don't understand this repo.)\n\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"albertlarsan68\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/102861/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/102861/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}